      "data": {
        "summary": "CVE-2024-52046 is a critical (CVSS 9.8) unsafe Java deserialization vulnerability in Apache MINA's ObjectSerializationDecoder, affecting all 2.0.x, 2.1.x, and 2.2.x releases. A remote, unauthenticated attacker who can deliver specially crafted serialized data can achieve Remote Code Execution (RCE). The EPSS score places this in the 97.6th percentile, indicating very high real-world exploitation likelihood despite no confirmed public exploit at this time.",
        "severity": "critical",
        "confidence": "high",
        "recommended_action": "SSVC: Attend \u2014 EPSS 97.6th percentile + CVSS 9.8 RCE warrants patching ahead of standard timelines. Upgrade to 2.0.27, 2.1.10, or 2.2.4. Patching alone is insufficient: explicitly allowlist accepted classes in ObjectSerializationDecoder via the new accept() methods. Only apps using IoBuffer#getObject() or ObjectSerializationCodecFactory are affected. Interim: remove ObjectSerializationCodecFactory, apply network segmentation.",
